      "amount": "1 teaspoon",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "Water",
      "amount": "1 cup",
      "notes": "For soaking garlic"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Soak the garlic cloves in water for at least 30 minutes to remove some of their pungency.",
    "Drain the garlic and pat it dry with a paper towel.",
    "Cut the garlic cloves into small pieces and mix with olive oil, lime juice, and salt in a bowl.",
    "Scoop up a small portion of the garlic mixture with your hand and shape it into a nigiri.",
    "Repeat the process until all the garlic mixture is used up."
  ],
